<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-651-770  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 651 770.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  June 25 1990 v218 n26A pS16(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Metamorphosis of a network. (Sonet optical fiber networkinterface) (Sonet Special supplement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilson, Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sonet, the optical fiber telecommunications network interface, isexpected to replace the current asynchronous, non-standard networktechnology that uses T1 communications digital transmission.andP;  Asynchronous network system, Sonet will eventually provide amultivendor broadband optical communications standard.andP;  It isexpected to facilitate simpler, stronger network operations bypermitting the elimination of fiber terminals, multiplexors, maindistribution frames and channel banks.andP;  Current distinctionsbetween switching and transmission may be reduced as well, so thattraining will be easier and one set of workers could control bothparts of the network.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SONET (Computer Network Protocol)BroadbandFiber opticsStandards.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>